#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn24.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Sotāpattivagga "
msgstr "1. Stream-Entry "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 6. Karotosutta → karatosuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn24.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Karotosutta "
msgstr "6. Acting "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.209, sc1
msgctxt "sn24.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:1.2"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise: "

# NOTE: Surely here karoto karayato must mean “punish”. Also see my note on AN 3.50 for ekagarika.
#. VAR: karoto → karato (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn24.6:1.3"
msgid "‘karoto kārayato chindato chedāpayato pacato pācāpayato socato socāpayato kilamato kilamāpayato phandato phandāpayato pāṇamatipātayato adinnaṃ ādiyato sandhiṃ chindato nillopaṃ harato ekāgārikaṃ karoto paripanthe tiṭṭhato paradāraṃ gacchato musā bhaṇato karoto na karīyati pāpaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Nothing bad is done by the doer when they punish, mutilate, torture, aggrieve, oppress, intimidate, or when they encourage others to do the same. Nothing bad is done when they kill, steal, break into houses, plunder wealth, steal from isolated buildings, commit highway robbery, commit adultery, and lie. "

# NOTE: The chakram is a reasonably well-known weapon, named as such in popular culture, so I see no reason not to use the Indic form. As usual, wikipedia and similar sources ignore the Buddhist usage, claiming that the earliest reference to this is in the Mahabharata. Note also that the use of papa is different to the Buddhist. Here papa is more primitive, a kind of effect of bad things rather than a psychological motivation.
msgctxt "sn24.6:1.4"
msgid "Khurapariyantena cepi cakkena yo imissā pathaviyā pāṇe ekamaṃsakhalaṃ ekamaṃsapuñjaṃ kareyya, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo. "
msgstr "If you were to reduce all the living creatures of this earth to one heap and mass of flesh with a razor-edged chakram, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil. "

msgctxt "sn24.6:1.5"
msgid "Dakkhiṇañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya; hananto ghātento chindanto chedāpento pacanto pācento, natthi tatonidānaṃ pāpaṃ, natthi pāpassa āgamo. "
msgstr "If you were to go along the south bank of the Ganges killing, mutilating, and torturing, and encouraging others to do the same, no evil comes of that, and no outcome of evil. "

msgctxt "sn24.6:1.6"
msgid "Uttarañcepi gaṅgāya tīraṃ gaccheyya; dadanto dāpento yajanto yajāpento, natthi tatonidānaṃ puññaṃ, natthi puññassa āgamo. "
msgstr "If you were to go along the north bank of the Ganges giving and sacrificing and encouraging others to do the same, no merit comes of that, and no outcome of merit. "

msgctxt "sn24.6:1.7"
msgid "Dānena damena saṃyamena saccavajjena natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo’”ti. "
msgstr "In giving, self-control, restraint, and truthfulness there is no merit or outcome of merit’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:1.8"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn24.6:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.2"
msgid "‘karoto kārayato … pe … "
msgstr "‘The one who acts does nothing wrong … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.3"
msgid "natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo’ti. "
msgstr "there is no merit or outcome of merit.’ "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.4"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … pe … "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.5"
msgid "saññāya sati … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.7"
msgid "viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.8"
msgid "‘karoto kārayato … pe … "
msgstr "‘The one who acts does nothing wrong … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:2.9"
msgid "natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo’ti. "
msgstr "there is no merit or outcome of merit.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.4"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.5"
msgid "‘karoto … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.6"
msgid "natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.7"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.8"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.9"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.10"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.11"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.12"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.13"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.14"
msgid "‘karoto kārayato … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.15"
msgid "natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.16"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.17"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“That which is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.18"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.19"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?” "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.20"
msgid "‘karoto kārayato … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.6:3.21"
msgid "natthi puññaṃ natthi puññassa āgamo’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.6:3.22"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn24.6:4.1"
msgid "“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—"
msgstr "“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation, "

msgctxt "sn24.6:4.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti. "
msgstr "they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.6:4.3"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

